'''Bryan Josué Acosta Ramos''' (born 24 November 1993) is a Honduran [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[FC Dallas]] in [[Major League Soccer]].

==Club career==
Born in [[La Ceiba]], Acosta started his career with [[Real C.D. España|Real España]]. He made his senior debut for the club in 2013.

On 12 July 2017, Acosta signed a four-year deal with [[Segunda División]] side [[CD Tenerife]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clubdeportivotenerife.es/noticia/bryan-acosta-cuarto-fichaje-del-cd-tenerife|title=Bryan Acosta, cuarto fichaje del CD Tenerife|trans-title=Bryan Acosta, fourth signing of CD Tenerife|publisher=CD Tenerife|language=es|date=12 July 2017|accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref>

On 8 January 2019, Acosta signed as a [[Designated Player Rule|Designated Player]] for [[FC Dallas]] in [[MLS]].<ref>https://www.fcdallas.com/post/2019/01/08/fc-dallas-signs-honduran-midfielder-bryan-acosta-designated-player</ref>

