Acosta took over captaincy of Honduras U23 Football Team from his teammate Marcelo Espinal in 2016.

==Personal life==
He was born to Raymundo Acosta and Adilia Ramos.

Acosta had to receive permission from [[Real C.D. España|Real España]] to get a few hours off to marry his fiancée Mavis Hernández on Friday 21 August 2015,<ref>[http://www.diez.hn/futboldeprimera/871481-99/real-españa-da-permiso-a-bryan-acosta-para-contraer-matrimonio Real España da permiso a Bryan Acosta para contraer matrimonio] - Diez {{es|icon}}</ref>
a day before the club had to play the ''Clásico Sampedrano'' against [[C.D. Marathón|Marathón]]. The ceremony was led by former footballer [[Carlos Oliva]], but was not attended by any of his teammates because of the forthcoming derby game.<ref>[http://www.diez.hn/futboldeprimera/871559-99/futbolista-brayan-acosta-contrae-matrimonio-en-la-ceiba Futbolista Brayan Acosta contrae matrimonio en La Ceiba] - Diez {{es|icon}}</ref>

